      • getLogLevel

        public static int getLogLevel()
        Returns the level of logging that will be displayed.

      • setLogLevel

        public static void setLogLevel​(int logLevel)
        Sets the level of logging to display, where each level includes all those below it. The default level is LOG_LEVEL_NONE. Please ensure this is set to Log#ERROR or LOG_LEVEL_NONE before deploying your app to ensure no sensitive information is logged. The levels are:
        • Log#VERBOSE
        • Log#DEBUG
        • Log#INFO
        • Log#WARN
        • Log#ERROR
        • LOG_LEVEL_NONE
        Parameters:
        logLevel - The level of logcat logging that Parse should do.
